Class ResourceDemandCapturedEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.measurement.order.AbstractMeasurementEvent

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MeasurementEvent

    public class ResourceDemandCapturedEvent
extends AbstractMeasurementEvent
    An event for the fact that the amount of a certain resource a certain code section demands was captured. This implies that the section was completely executed.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors

      • ResourceDemandCapturedEvent

        public ResourceDemandCapturedEvent(CodeSection codeSection,
                                   java.lang.String type,
                                   double value)
        Creates an event for the fact that codeSection has been completely executed and demanded value resources of the type type.
        Parameters:
        codeSection - The code section that was executed. Must not be null.
        type - The demanded resource’s type. See ResourceDemandingInternalAction for a list of conventional strings. Must not be null.
        value - The resource demand’s value, expressed in the unit implied by type. Must not be negative.
